From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 17:15:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 19/19] Install Pulse deps before invoking manage.sh

Upstream issue: danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure (TBD) — bug
applies to every platform, not Nix-specific.

The v5.0 GUI/CLI installer's `installPulse()` in
PAI/PAI-Install/engine/actions.ts:1604 spawns `manage.sh install`,
which boots `pulse.ts` and probes :31337 for a successful bind. When
the bind fails, the wizard reports the cryptic message "Pulse install
command failed. Voice notifications will not be available."

Reproduction (NixOS — easiest surface; same root cause on macOS/Linux
fresh-install paths too):

  $ ./result/bin/pai --force-install
  ... wizard runs through detection, file copy, identity, voice ...
  ⚠  Pulse install command failed.

  $ tail ~/.claude/PAI/PULSE/logs/pulse-stderr.log
  error: Cannot find package 'smol-toml' from
  '/home/user/.claude/PAI/PULSE/pulse.ts'
  Bun v1.3.11 (Linux x64)

Root cause — the wizard's own migration step deletes the deps:

  1. The Nix wrapper `cp -r`s the read-only template into ~/.claude
     and runs `cd ~/.claude/PAI/PULSE && bun install` to populate
     node_modules.
  2. The wizard's `moveExistingClaudeToBackup` (actions.ts:605) then
     iterates ~/.claude/PAI/ and `rmSync(..., { recursive: true,
     force: true })` on every entry except PAI-Install (lines 654-
     663). PULSE/, including its freshly-installed node_modules, is
     wiped.
  3. `installFromLocalBundle` (actions.ts:1129) re-copies the bundle
     tree but its BUNDLE_COPY_EXCLUDES set (line 1074) deliberately
     skips node_modules — the bundle is never the source of deps.
  4. `installPulse` (actions.ts:1604) then spawns `manage.sh install`.
     manage.sh starts pulse.ts directly (Linux) or via launchd
     (macOS). pulse.ts's first import is `smol-toml`; without it,
     the daemon crashes before binding :31337. manage.sh's port-bind
     probe times out and exits 1. installPulse() reports failure.

The same flow exists on macOS (the wrapper isn't there to compensate),
which means this is an upstream bug, not Nix-specific. macOS users
who run `bash install.sh` cleanly hit the identical failure mode on
first install — the bundle never ships node_modules, and nothing in
the install path runs `bun install` for PULSE before manage.sh tries
to start the daemon.

Fix — add an explicit `bun install` step inside `installPulse()`,
before the `manage.sh install` spawn. The step is:

  - Idempotent: bun install is fast (~30ms) when the lockfile is
    satisfied, so the cost is negligible on hosts where deps happen
    to already be present.
  - Loud on failure: if bun install exits non-zero (registry
    unreachable, no network, lockfile mismatch), the wizard now
    surfaces the actual failure mode instead of swallowing it under
    the misleading "manage.sh install command failed" string and
    leaves the user a copy-paste recovery command.
  - Bounded: 180s timeout (cold network case for 109 packages),
    well within the wizard's "Voice + Pulse" step budget.

Files touched:

  - PAI/PAI-Install/engine/actions.ts (1 hunk, +30 lines)

Verification on NixOS after this patch:

  $ ./result/bin/pai --force-install
  ... wizard runs ...
  ✓ Pulse installed and running on port 31337.
  $ curl -s http://localhost:31337/notify -d '{"message":"","voice_enabled":false}'
  (200 OK — :31337 bound)

  $ ls ~/.claude/PAI/PULSE/node_modules/smol-toml
  dist  LICENSE  package.json  README.md

This patch is intentionally upstream-shaped — it fixes the bug for
every PAI v5.0 user, not just Nix users. The Nix wrapper's own
`cd PULSE && bun install` line in default.nix becomes redundant
after this patch (the wizard now guarantees deps), but is kept as a
defensive belt-and-braces measure: if a future upstream change moves
Pulse deps elsewhere or skips this function, the wrapper's earlier
install still produces a usable tree the user can run pulse from
manually.
---
 .../v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PAI-Install/engine/actions.ts          | 30 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 30 insertions(+)

--- a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PAI-Install/engine/actions.ts
+++ b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PAI-Install/engine/actions.ts
@@ -1610,6 +1610,36 @@
     return false;
   }

+  // Ensure Pulse's runtime dependencies are installed before invoking
+  // manage.sh. The wizard's earlier `moveExistingClaudeToBackup` clears
+  // ~/.claude/PAI/* (everything except PAI-Install) and the subsequent
+  // `installFromLocalBundle` deliberately excludes node_modules from the
+  // bundle copy. Net effect: by the time we reach this function, the
+  // freshly-laid PULSE tree has no node_modules. pulse.ts's first import
+  // is `smol-toml`; without it the daemon crashes on boot, manage.sh's
+  // port-bind probe never sees :31337, and the user gets the mysterious
+  // "Pulse install command failed" with no actionable signal.
+  // bun install is idempotent and fast when the lockfile is satisfied,
+  // so the cost is negligible on hosts where deps already happen to be
+  // present (e.g. NixOS where the wrapper pre-populates them — though
+  // those get wiped by the migration step on first install too).
+  await emit({ event: "progress", step: "voice", percent: 10, detail: "Installing Pulse dependencies..." });
+
+  const depsOk = await new Promise<boolean>((resolve) => {
+    const child = spawn("bun", ["install"], {
+      cwd: pulseDir,
+      stdio: ["ignore", "pipe", "pipe"],
+    });
+    const timer = setTimeout(() => { child.kill(); resolve(false); }, 180000);
+    child.on("close", (code) => { clearTimeout(timer); resolve(code === 0); });
+    child.on("error", () => { clearTimeout(timer); resolve(false); });
+  });
+
+  if (!depsOk) {
+    await emit({ event: "message", content: "Pulse dependency install failed (bun install in PAI/PULSE). Voice notifications will be unavailable. Retry manually: cd ~/.claude/PAI/PULSE && bun install && bash manage.sh install" });
+    return false;
+  }
+
   await emit({ event: "progress", step: "voice", percent: 20, detail: "Installing Pulse (voice + dashboard + observability)..." });

   try {
